verses.verse: A Song <S%H7892><s%> of degrees <S%H4609><s%> of David. <S%H1732><s%> Behold, <S%H2009><s%> how <S%H4100><s%> good <S%H2896><s%> and how <S%H4100><s%> pleasant <S%H5273><s%> it is for brothers <S%H251><s%> to dwell <S%H3427><s%> together <S%H3162><s%> in unity! <S%H3162><s%>

It is like the precious <S%H2896><s%> ointment <S%H8081><s%> on the head, <S%H7218><s%> that ran <S%H3331><s%> down <S%H3381><s%> on the beard, <S%H2206><s%> even Aaron's <S%H175><s%> beard: <S%H2206><s%> that went <S%H3381><s%> down <S%H3381><s%> to the skirts <S%H6310><s%> of his garments; <S%H4060><s%>

As the dew <S%H2919><s%> of Hermon, <S%H2768><s%> and as the dew that descended <S%H3381><s%> on the mountains <S%H2042><s%> of Zion: <S%H6726><s%> for there <S%H8033><s%> the LORD <S%H3068><s%> commanded <S%H6680><s%> the blessing, <S%H1293><s%> even life <S%H2416><s%> for ever more. <S%H5769><s%>
